==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Countermure
<hw>Coun"ter*mure`</hw> <pr>(-m?r`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Counter-</ets> + <ets>mure</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>contremur</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Fort.)</fld> <def>A wall raised
behind another, to supply its place when breached or destroyed.
<mark>[R.]</mark> Cf. <er>Contramure</er>.</def>
<rj><au>Knolles.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Countermure</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Countermure
<hw>Coun`ter*mure"</hw> <pr>(koun`t?r-m?r")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Countermured</conjf>
<pr>(-m?rd")</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Countermuring</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>contremurer</ets>.]</ety> <def>To fortify with a wall behind
another wall.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Kyd.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Counternatural</ent>⟦br⟧
